{"pr_number": 894, "pr_title": "Handle output in json-formatter", "pr_createdAt": "2020-02-10T16:49:57Z", "pr_url": "https://github.com/cucumber/common/pull/894", "timeline": [{"oid": "bfe7bbe7ddea8044e1cf13d764943d2eec2a75e3", "url": "https://github.com/cucumber/common/commit/bfe7bbe7ddea8044e1cf13d764943d2eec2a75e3", "message": "Add feature file showing how output is handled", "committedDate": "2020-02-10T16:08:39Z", "type": "commit"}, {"oid": "6799539c45adcec48a1547af606beb2c51ca5f0f", "url": "https://github.com/cucumber/common/commit/6799539c45adcec48a1547af606beb2c51ca5f0f", "message": "json-formatter: ensure JS ndjson are regenerated when changing step definitions", "committedDate": "2020-02-10T16:25:08Z", "type": "commit"}, {"oid": "303a49e81af9884a18d1497817be72cf44078eb9", "url": "https://github.com/cucumber/common/commit/303a49e81af9884a18d1497817be72cf44078eb9", "message": "json-formatyter: handle attachments with type text/output as outputs", "committedDate": "2020-02-10T16:44:30Z", "type": "commit"}, {"oid": "4a05af1fa82b3d7fce68b95d281fd8b3ada557c8", "url": "https://github.com/cucumber/common/commit/4a05af1fa82b3d7fce68b95d281fd8b3ada557c8", "message": "Use proper name for variables", "committedDate": "2020-02-10T16:51:41Z", "type": "commit"}, {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDM3NzM4MTc5NQ==", "url": "https://github.com/cucumber/common/pull/894#discussion_r377381795", "bodyText": "text/output is not a valid media type. It should be text/plain. Alternatively, it should be an extension - I suggest text/x.cucumber.output+plain.", "author": "aslakhellesoy", "createdAt": "2020-02-10T23:39:06Z", "path": "json-formatter/javascript/features/step_definitions/steps.ts", "diffHunk": "@@ -8,6 +8,10 @@ Given('a passed {word} with text attachment {string}', function(word: string, at\n   this.attach(attachmentText, 'text/plain')\n })\n \n+Given('a step outputs:', function(txt: string) {\n+  this.attach(txt, 'text/output')", "originalCommit": "4a05af1fa82b3d7fce68b95d281fd8b3ada557c8", "replyToReviewId": null, "replies": [{"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDM3NzU1MDU4MQ==", "url": "https://github.com/cucumber/common/pull/894#discussion_r377550581", "bodyText": "sounds fine, I was definitely not convinced by text/output anyway, sounded too hacky :D", "author": "vincent-psarga", "createdAt": "2020-02-11T10:29:24Z", "replyToReviewId": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDM3NzM4MTc5NQ=="}], "type": "inlineReview"}, {"oid": "d9145e7627bb1a67f0074ddc122cc77a018bf547", "url": "https://github.com/cucumber/common/commit/d9145e7627bb1a67f0074ddc122cc77a018bf547", "message": "Use a better media type for output attachments", "committedDate": "2020-02-11T10:36:59Z", "type": "commit"}, {"oid": "3322fee436bbc4da5061cc25875e0d6ffb4f2723", "url": "https://github.com/cucumber/common/commit/3322fee436bbc4da5061cc25875e0d6ffb4f2723", "message": "fake-cucumber: added a `log` function to World which will add specific attachments", "committedDate": "2020-02-11T10:49:16Z", "type": "commit"}, {"oid": "bd2958d38834739e9c4372a1a135f39f413f4939", "url": "https://github.com/cucumber/common/commit/bd2958d38834739e9c4372a1a135f39f413f4939", "message": "Use media-type \"text/x.cucumber.log+plain\" for attachments (instead of \"text/x.cucumber.output+plain\")", "committedDate": "2020-02-12T13:21:44Z", "type": "commit"}, {"oid": "f8a0db4fbf3d79dcd92b15cd8f97aadecd8da3c2", "url": "https://github.com/cucumber/common/commit/f8a0db4fbf3d79dcd92b15cd8f97aadecd8da3c2", "message": "Merge branch 'master' into json-formatter-handle-text-attachments-as-output", "committedDate": "2020-02-21T10:49:31Z", "type": "commit"}, {"oid": "8acd0332e95372a74c9ee572cb14861609645df5", "url": "https://github.com/cucumber/common/commit/8acd0332e95372a74c9ee572cb14861609645df5", "message": "Update changelog", "committedDate": "2020-02-21T13:13:06Z", "type": "commit"}]}